CubeProvider` |\n25: | `agentcube/operations/__init__.py` | Placeholder module docstring (no symbols) |\n26: | `examples/hello-agent/main.py` | Example agent |\n27: | `examples/math-agent/main.py` | Example agent |\n28: \n29: **Setuptools packages** (from `pyproject.toml` `[tool.setuptools]`):  \n30: `agentcube`, `agentcube.cli`, `agentcube.runtime`, `agentcube.operations`, `agentcube.services`  \n31: *(Note: `agentcube.models` is not listed in `[tool.setuptools] packages` but is imported; packaging may rely on setuptools discovery for subpackages — reconstruct imports from source as above.)*\n32: \n33: ## Console script entry point\n34: \n35: ```toml\n36: [project.scripts]\n37: kubectl-agentcube = \"agentcube.cli.main:app\"\n38: ```\n39: \n40: Typer app object: `app = typer.Typer(name=\"agentcube\", help=\"...\", no_args_is_help=True, rich_markup_mode=\"rich\", add_completion=False)`.\n41: \n42: ## Typer — root callback\n43: \n44: ```python\n45: def main(\n46:     version: Optional[bool] = typer.Option(\n47:         None, \"--version\", help=\"Show version and exit\",\n48:         callback=version_callback, is_eager=True,\n49:     ),\n50:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", \"-v\", help=\"Enable verbose output\"),\n51: ) -> None:\n52:     \"\"\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\"\"\"\n53: ```\n54: \n55: ## Typer — `pack`\n56: \n57: ```python\n58: def pack(\n59:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n60:     agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n61:     language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n62:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n63:     port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n64:     build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n65:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n66:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n67:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n68: ) -> None:\n69: ```\n70: \n71: ## Typer — `build`\n72: \n73: ```python\n74: def build(\n75:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n76:     proxy: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"-p\", \"--proxy\", help=\"Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\"),\n77:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n78:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for build artifacts\"),\n79:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n80: ) -> None:\n81: ```\n82: \n83: ## Typer — `publish`\n84: \n85: ```python\n86: def publish(\n87:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n88:     version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\", help=\"Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\"),\n89:     image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-url\", help=\"Image repository URL (required in local build mode)\"),\n90:     image_username: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-username\", help=\"Username for image repository\"),\n91:     image_password: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-password\", help=\"Password for image repository\"),\n92:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n93:     region: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--region\", help=\"Deployment region\"),\n94:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n95:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n96:     node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--node-port\", help=\"Specific NodePort to use (30000-32767) for K8s deployment\"),\n97:     replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--replicas\", help=\"Number of replicas for K8s deployment (default: 1)\"),\n98:     namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--namespace\", help=\"The namespace for the deployment\"),\n99:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n100: ) -> None:\n101: ```\n102: \n103: ## Typer — `invoke`\n104: \n105: ```python\n106: def invoke(\n107:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n108:     payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent\"),\n109:     header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", help=\"Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Can be specified multiple times.\"),\n110:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n111:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n112: ) -> None:\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ## Typer — `status`\n116: \n117: ```python\n118: def status(\n119:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n120:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n121:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n122: ) -> None:\n123: ```\n124: \n125: ## Helper functions (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n126: \n127: ```python\n128: def version_callback(value: bool) -> None: ...\n129: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None: ...  # prints, typer.Exit(1)\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ## Runtime classes\n133: \n134: ### `PackRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`)\n135: \n136: ```python\n137: class PackRuntime:\n138:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n139:     def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n140:     def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n141:     def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n142:     def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n143:     def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n144:     def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n145:     def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n146:     def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n147:     def _process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n148:     def _process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n149:     def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]: ...\n150:     def _generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str: ...\n151:     def _generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str: ...\n152:     def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None: ...\n153:     def _prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path: ...\n154:     def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str: ...\n155: ```\n156: \n157: ### `BuildRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`)\n158: \n159: ```python\n160: class BuildRuntime:\n161:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n162:     def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n163:     def _increment_version(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata) -> Any: ...\n164:     def _validate_build_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n165:     def _build_local(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n166:     def _build_cloud(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n167:     def _update_build_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, build_result: Dict[str, str], tag: str = \"latest\") -> None: ...\n168: ```\n169: \n170: ### `PublishRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`)\n171: \n172: ```python\n173: class PublishRuntime:\n174:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n175:     def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n176:     def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n177:     def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n178:     def _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n179:     def _prepare_local_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n180:     def _prepare_cloud_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n181:     def _update_publish_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, agent_info: Dict[str, Any]) -> None: ...\n182: ```\n183: \n184: ### `InvokeRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`)\n185: \n186: ```python\n187: class InvokeRuntime:\n188:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n189:     def invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Any: ...\n190:     def _validate_invoke_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> Tuple[Any, str, str]: ...\n191:     async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(self, agent_id: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], endpoint: str, workspace_path: Path) -> Any: ...\n192:     async def _direct_http_invocation(self, endpoint: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], workspace_path: Path) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n193: ```\n194: \n195: **Implementation note:** `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` only assigns `response` inside `if endpoint.startswith(\"http\"):`; if the condition is false, `return response` may raise `UnboundLocalError` (as of extracted source).\n196: \n197: ### `StatusRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`)\n198: \n199: ```python\n200: class StatusRuntime:\n201:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n202:     def get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n203:     def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n204:     def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n205: ```\n206: \n207: ## AR-023: `invoke` command — Technical Implementation\n208: \n209: ### Command Flow\n210: \n211: ```\n212: ┌─────────────────┐     ┌──────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n213: │  CLI (main.py)  │────▶│  InvokeRuntime    │────▶│  HTTP Client    │\n214: │  - parse args   │     │  - validate       │     │  - POST /invoke │\n215: │  - parse JSON   │     │  - build URL      │     │  - headers      │\n216: │  - parse headers│     │  - invoke         │     │  - response     │\n217: └─────────────────┘     └──────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n218: ```\n219: \n220: ### CLI Layer (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n221: \n222: **Function signature:**\n223: ```python\n224: def invoke(\n225:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n226:     payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent\"),\n227:     header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", help=\"Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Can be specified multiple times.\"),\n228:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n229:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n230: ) -> None:\n231: ```\n232: \n233: **Implementation:**\n234: ```python\n235: def invoke(\n236:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", ...),\n237:     payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", ...),\n238:     header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", ...),\n239:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", ...),\n240:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", ...),\n241: ) -> None:\n242:     import json\n243:     from pathlib import Path\n244:     from rich.console import Console\n245:     from rich.progress import Progress, SpinnerColumn, TextColumn\n246:     \n247:     console = Console()\n248:     workspace_path = Path(workspace).expanduser().resolve()\n249:     \n250:     # Parse payload JSON (early validation)\n251:     try:\n252:         payload_dict = json.loads(payload)\n253:     except json.JSONDecodeError as e:\n254:         console.print(f\"[red]Error: Invalid JSON payload: {e}[/red]\")\n255:         raise typer.Exit(1)\n256:     \n257:     # Parse headers\n258:     headers = {}\n259:     if header_list:\n260:         for header in header_list:\n261:             if \":\" not in header:\n262:                 console.print(f\"[red]Error: Invalid header format '{header}'. Expected 'key:value'[/red]\")\n263:                 raise typer.Exit(1)\n264:             key, value = header.split(\":\", 1)\n265:             headers[key.strip()] = value.strip()\n266:     \n267:     # Execute with progress indicator\n268:     with Progress(\n269:         SpinnerColumn(),\n270:         TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n271:         console=console,\n272:     ) as progress:\n273:         task = progress.add_task(\"Invoking agent...\", total=None)\n274:         try:\n275:             runtime = InvokeRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n276:             result = runtime.invoke(workspace_path, payload_dict, headers if headers else None)\n277:             progress.update(task, completed=True)\n278:             console.print(\"[green]✓ Invocation successful[/green]\")\n279:             # Display result (format based on response type)\n280:             if isinstance(result, dict):\n281:                 console.print_json(json.dumps(result, indent=2))\n282:             else:\n283:                 console.print(result)\n284:         except Exception as e:\n285:             progress.update(task, completed=True)\n286:             _handle_error(e, \"invoking agent\", verbose)\n287: ```\n288: \n289: ### Runtime Layer (`agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`)\n290: \n291: **Class structure:**\n292: ```python\n293: import httpx\n294: import asyncio\n295: from pathlib import Path\n296: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional, Tuple\n297: from agentcube.services.metadata_service import MetadataService\n298: from agentcube.services.agentcube_provider import AgentCubeProvider\n299: from agentcube.services.k8s_provider import KubernetesProvider\n300: \n301: class InvokeRuntime:\n302:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n303:     \n304:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n305:         self.verbose = verbose\n306:         self.provider = provider\n307:         self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n308:         self.logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n309:     \n310:     def invoke(\n311:         self,\n312:         workspace_path: Path,\n313:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n314:         headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None\n315:     ) -> Any:\n316:         # Validate prerequisites and get metadata + endpoint\n317:         metadata, endpoint, agent_type = self._validate_invoke_prerequisites(workspace_path)\n318:         \n319:         # Merge session_id from metadata if available\n320:         if headers is None:\n321:             headers = {}\n322:         if metadata.session_id:\n323:             headers[self.SESSION_HEADER] = metadata.session_id\n324:         \n325:         # Route based on provider\n326:         if self.provider == \"agentcube\":\n327:             return asyncio.run(\n328:                 self._invoke_agent_via_agentcube(\n329:                     agent_id=metadata.agent_id,\n330:                     payload=payload,\n331:                     headers=headers,\n332:                     endpoint=endpoint,\n333:                     workspace_path=workspace_path\n334:                 )\n335:             )\n336:         elif self.provider == \"k8s\":\n337:             return asyncio.run(\n338:                 self._direct_http_invocation(\n339:                     endpoint=endpoint,\n340:                     payload=payload,\n341:                     headers=headers,\n342:                     workspace_path=workspace_path\n343:                 )\n344:             )\n345:         else:\n346:             raise ValueError(f\"Unknown provider: {self.provider}\")\n347:     \n348:     def _validate_invoke_prerequisites(\n349:         self,\n350:         workspace_path: Path\n351:     ) -> Tuple[Any, str, str]:\n352:         \"\"\"Validate workspace and return (metadata, endpoint, agent_type).\"\"\"\n353:         # Load metadata\n354:         metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n355:         \n356:         # Check if published\n357:         if not metadata.agent_id:\n358:             raise ValueError(\n359:                 \"Agent has not been published. Run 'kubectl-agentcube publish' first.\"\n360:             )\n361:         \n362:         # Determine endpoint based on deployment type\n363:         if metadata.k8s_deployment:\n364:             deployment_type = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"type\", \"unknown\")\n365:             if deployment_type == \"AgentRuntime\":\n366:                 # AgentRuntime CR: construct invocation URL\n367:                 namespace = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\")\n368:                 agent_name = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"name\", metadata.agent_name)\n369:                 router_url = metadata.router_url or metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"router_url\")\n370:                 if not router_url:\n371:                     raise ValueError(\n372:                         \"router_url is required for AgentRuntime invocation. \"\n373:                         \"Ensure it is set in agent_metadata.yaml\"\n374:                     )\n375:                 endpoint = (\n376:                     f\"{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/\"\n377:                     f\"agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n378:                 )\n379:                 return metadata, endpoint, \"agentruntime\"\n380:             elif deployment_type == \"Deployment\":\n381:                 # Standard K8s Deployment: use agent_endpoint\n382:                 if not metadata.agent_endpoint:\n383:                     raise ValueError(\n384:                         \"agent_endpoint is required for Deployment invocation. \"\n385:                         \"Ensure it is set in agent_metadata.yaml\"\n386:                     )\n387:                 return metadata, metadata.agent_endpoint, \"deployment\"\n388:             else:\n389:                 raise ValueError(f\"Unknown deployment type: {deployment_type}\")\n390:         else:\n391:             # Fallback to agent_endpoint\n392:             if not metadata.agent_endpoint:\n393:                 raise ValueError(\n394:                     \"No agent_endpoint found in metadata. \"\n395:                     \"Agent may not be published correctly.\"\n396:                 )\n397:             return metadata, metadata.agent_endpoint, \"unknown\"\n398:     \n399:     async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(\n400:         self,\n401:         agent_id: str,\n402:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n403:         headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n404:         endpoint: str,\n405:         workspace_path: Path\n406:     ) -> Any:\n407:         \"\"\"Invoke agent through AgentCube Router.\"\"\"\n408:         if not endpoint.startswith(\"http\"):\n409:             # Fix for UnboundLocalError: initialize response\n410:             raise ValueError(f\"Invalid endpoint URL: {endpoint}\")\n411:         \n412:         async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n413:             response = await client.post(\n414:                 endpoint,\n415:                 json=payload,\n416:                 headers=headers,\n417:                 timeout=120.0\n418:             )\n419:             response.raise_for_status()\n420:             return response.json()\n421:     \n422:     async def _direct_http_invocation(\n423:         self,\n424:         endpoint: str,\n425:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n426:         headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n427:         workspace_path: Path\n428:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n429:         \"\"\"Direct HTTP invocation for standard K8s Deployment.\"\"\"\n430:         async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n431:             response = await client.post(\n432:                 endpoint,\n433:                 json=payload,\n434:                 headers=headers,\n435:                 timeout=120.0\n436:             )\n437:             response.raise_for_status()\n438:             return response.json()\n439: ```\n440: \n441: ### Error Handling\n442: \n443: | Error | Source | CLI Output | Exit Code |\n444: |-------|--------|------------|-----------|\n445: | Invalid JSON payload | `json.loads()` | `[red]Error: Invalid JSON payload: {details}[/red]` | 1 |\n446: | Invalid header format | Header parsing | `[red]Error: Invalid header format '{header}'. Expected 'key:value'[/red]` | 1 |\n447: | Agent not published | `_validate_invoke_prerequisites` | `[red]Error invoking agent: Agent has not been published...[/red]` | 1 |\n448: | Missing router_url | `_validate_invoke_prerequisites` | `[red]Error invoking agent: router_url is required...[/red]` | 1 |\n449: | Missing agent_endpoint | `_validate_invoke_prerequisites` | `[red]Error invoking agent: agent_endpoint is required...[/red]` | 1 |\n450: | HTTP error | `httpx` | `[red]Error invoking agent: {status_code} {reason}[/red]` | 1 |\n451: | Timeout | `httpx.TimeoutException` | `[red]Error invoking agent: Request timed out after 120s[/red]` | 1 |\n452: \n453: ## AR-023: `status` command — Technical Implementation\n454: \n455: ### Command Flow\n456: \n457: ```\n458: ┌─────────────────┐     ┌──────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n459: │  CLI (main.py)  │────▶│  StatusRuntime    │────▶│  Provider       │\n460: │  - parse args   │     │  - get_status     │     │  - K8s API      │\n461: │  - display      │     │  - route          │     │  - CRD API      │\n462: └─────────────────┘     └──────────────────┘     └──────────────────┘\n463:                               │\n464:                               ▼\n465:                        ┌─────────────────┐\n466:                        │  Rich Table     │\n467:                        │  - status       │\n468:                        │  - endpoint     │\n469:                        │  - pods         │\n470:                        └─────────────────┘\n471: ```\n472: \n473: ### CLI Layer (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n474: \n475: **Function signature:**\n476: ```python\n477: def status(\n478:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n479:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n480:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n481: ) -> None:\n482: ```\n483: \n484: **Implementation:**\n485: ```python\n486: def status(\n487:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", ...),\n488:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", ...),\n489:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", ...),\n490: ) -> None:\n491:     from pathlib import Path\n492:     from rich.console import Console\n493:     from rich.table import Table\n494:     from rich.progress import Progress, SpinnerColumn, TextColumn\n495:     \n496:     console = Console()\n497:     workspace_path = Path(workspace).expanduser().resolve()\n498:     \n499:     with Progress(\n500:         SpinnerColumn(),\n501:         TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n502:         console=console,\n503:     ) as progress:\n504:         task = progress.add_task(\"Fetching agent status...\", total=None)\n505:         try:\n506:             runtime = StatusRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n507:             status_info = runtime.get_status(workspace_path, provider=provider)\n508:             progress.update(task, completed=True)\n509:             \n510:             # Check for not_published status\n511:             if status_info.get(\"status\") == \"not_published\":\n512:                 console.print(\"[yellow]⚠ Agent has not been published[/yellow]\")\n513:                 console.print(\n514:                     \"\\nRun [bold]kubectl-agentcube publish[/bold] to deploy your agent.\\n\"\n515:                 )\n516:                 raise typer.Exit(1)\n517:             \n518:             # Check for error status\n519:             if status_info.get(\"status\") == \"error\":\n520:                 console.print(f\"[red]✗ Status error: {status_info.get('error', 'Unknown error')}[/red]\")\n521:                 raise typer.Exit(1)\n522:             \n523:             # Display status table\n524:             table = Table(title=f\"Agent Status: {status_info.get('agent_name', 'Unknown')}\")\n525:             table.add_column(\"Property\", style=\"cyan\")\n526:             table.add_column(\"Value\", style=\"green\")\n527:             \n528:             # Core status\n529:             table.add_row(\"Status\", status_info.get(\"status\", \"unknown\"))\n530:             if status_info.get(\"agent_endpoint\"):\n531:                 table.add_row(\"Endpoint\", status_info[\"agent_endpoint\"])\n532:             if status_info.get(\"deployment_type\"):\n533:                 table.add_row(\"Deployment Type\", status_info[\"deployment_type\"])\n534:             if status_info.get(\"namespace\"):\n535:                 table.add_row(\"Namespace\", status_info[\"namespace\"])\n536:             \n537:             # Pod status (if available)\n538:             if \"pods\" in status_info:\n539:                 pod_info = status_info[\"pods\"]\n540:                 table.add_row(\n541:                     \"Pods\",\n542:                     f\"{pod_info.get('ready', 0)}/{pod_info.get('total', 0)} ready\"\n543:                 )\n544:             \n545:             # Replicas (for K8s deployment)\n546:             if status_info.get(\"replicas\") is not None:\n547:                 table.add_row(\"Replicas\", str(status_info[\"replicas\"]))\n548:             \n549:             # Session info (if available)\n550:             if status_info.get(\"session_id\"):\n551:                 table.add_row(\"Session ID\", status_info[\"session_id\"])\n552:             \n553:             console.print(table)\n554:             \n555:         except Exception as e:\n556:             progress.update(task, completed=True)\n557:             _handle_error(e, \"fetching status\", verbose)\n558: ```\n559: \n560: ### Runtime Layer (`agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`)\n561: \n562: **Class structure:**\n563: ```python\n564: import logging\n565: from pathlib import Path\n566: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n567: from agentcube.services.metadata_service import MetadataService\n568: from agentcube.services.k8s_provider import KubernetesProvider\n569: from agentcube.services.agentcube_provider import AgentCubeProvider\n570: \n571: class StatusRuntime:\n572:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n573:         self.verbose = verbose\n574:         self.provider = provider\n575:         self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n576:         self.logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n577:     \n578:     def get_status(\n579:         self,\n580:         workspace_path: Path,\n581:         provider: Optional[str] = None\n582:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n583:         \"\"\"Get comprehensive agent status.\"\"\"\n584:         if provider is None:\n585:             provider = self.provider\n586:         \n587:         # Load metadata\n588:         try:\n589:             metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n590:         except FileNotFoundError:\n591:             return {\n592:                 \"status\": \"not_found\",\n593:                 \"error\": f\"Metadata not found at {workspace_path}\"\n594:             }\n595:         \n596:         # Check if published\n597:         if not metadata.agent_id:\n598:             return {\n599:                 \"status\": \"not_published\",\n600:                 \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name\n601:             }\n602:         \n603:         # Build base status\n604:         status_info = {\n605:             \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n606:             \"agent_id\": metadata.agent_id,\n607:             \"session_id\": metadata.session_id,\n608:             \"deployment_type\": metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"type\", \"unknown\") if metadata.k8s_deployment else \"unknown\",\n609:             \"namespace\": metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\") if metadata.k8s_deployment else \"default\",\n610:         }\n611:         \n612:         # Route to appropriate status getter\n613:         if metadata.k8s_deployment:\n614:             deployment_type = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"type\", \"unknown\")\n615:             if deployment_type == \"AgentRuntime\":\n616:                 cr_status = self._get_cr_k8s_status(metadata)\n617:                 status_info.update(cr_status)\n618:             elif deployment_type == \"Deployment\":\n619:                 k8s_status = self._get_k8s_status(metadata)\n620:                 status_info.update(k8s_status)\n621:             else:\n622:                 status_info[\"status\"] = \"unknown_deployment_type\"\n623:         else:\n624:             status_info[\"status\"] = \"unknown\"\n625:         \n626:         return status_info\n627:     \n628:     def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n629:         \"\"\"Get status for standard K8s Deployment.\"\"\"\n630:         try:\n631:             k8s_provider = KubernetesProvider(\n632:                 namespace=metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\"),\n633:                 verbose=self.verbose\n634:             )\n635:             \n636:             deployment_name = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"deployment_name\")\n637:             if not deployment_name:\n638:                 return {\"status\": \"error\", \"error\": \"deployment_name not found in metadata\"}\n639:             \n640:             # Get deployment status\n641:             deployment_info = k8s_provider.get_agent_status(deployment_name)\n642:             \n643:             # Extract pod information\n644:             pods = deployment_info.get(\"pods\", [])\n645:             ready_pods = sum(1 for p in pods if p.get(\"ready\", False))\n646:             \n647:             return {\n648:                 \"status\": deployment_info.get(\"status\", \"unknown\"),\n649:                 \"agent_endpoint\": metadata.agent_endpoint,\n650:                 \"replicas\": deployment_info.get(\"replicas\", 1),\n651:                 \"pods\": {\n652:                     \"total\": len(pods),\n653:                     \"ready\": ready_pods,\n654:                     \"details\": pods\n655:                 }\n656:             }\n657:         except Exception as e:\n658:             self.logger.error(f\"Error getting K8s status: {e}\")\n659:             return {\n660:                 \"status\": \"error\",\n661:                 \"error\": str(e)\n662:             }\n663:     \n664:     def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n665:         \"\"\"Get status for AgentRuntime CR.\"\"\"\n666:         try:\n667:             agentcube_provider = AgentCubeProvider(\n668:                 namespace=metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\"),\n669:                 verbose=self.verbose\n670:             )\n671:             \n672:             agent_name = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"name\", metadata.agent_name)\n673:             \n674:             # Get AgentRuntime CR\n675:             cr_object = agentcube_provider.get_agent_runtime(\n676:                 name=agent_name,\n677:                 namespace=metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\")\n678:             )\n679:             \n680:             if cr_object is None:\n681:                 return {\n682:                     \"status\": \"not_found\",\n683:                     \"error\": f\"AgentRuntime '{agent_name}' not found in namespace '{metadata.k8s_deployment.get('namespace', 'default')}'\"\n684:                 }\n685:             \n686:             # Extract status from CR\n687:             cr_status = cr_object.get(\"status\", {})\n688:             status = cr_status.get(\"status\", \"created_no_status\")\n689:             endpoint = cr_status.get(\"agentEndpoint\", metadata.agent_endpoint)\n690:             \n691:             return {\n692:                 \"status\": status,\n693:                 \"agent_endpoint\": endpoint,\n694:                 \"session_id\": metadata.session_id,\n695:             }\n696:         except Exception as e:\n697:             self.logger.error(f\"Error getting CR status: {e}\")\n698:             return {\n699:                 \"status\": \"error\",\n700:                 \"error\": str(e)\n701:             }\n702: ```\n703: \n704: ### Status Response Schema\n705: \n706: ```python\n707: # Successful status response (AgentRuntime CR)\n708: {\n709:     \"agent_name\": \"hello-agent\",\n710:     \"agent_id\": \"agent-12345\",\n711:     \"session_id\": \"session-abcde\",\n712:     \"status\": \"ready\",  # ready, pending, error, not_found\n713:     \"agent_endpoint\": \"http://router.example.com/v1/...\",\n714:     \"deployment_type\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n715:     \"namespace\": \"default\"\n716: }\n717: \n718: # Successful status response (K8s Deployment)\n719: {\n720:     \"agent_name\": \"hello-agent\",\n721:     \"agent_id\": \"agent-12345\",\n722:     \"session_id\": \"session-abcde\",\n723:     \"status\": \"ready\",\n724:     \"agent_endpoint\": \"http://node:30080\",\n725:     \"deployment_type\": \"Deployment\",\n726:     \"namespace\": \"default\",\n727:     \"replicas\": 1,\n728:     \"pods\": {\n729:         \"total\": 1,\n730:         \"ready\": 1,\n731:         \"details\": [\n732:             {\"name\": \"hello-agent-xxx\", \"ready\": True, \"phase\": \"Running\"}\n733:         ]\n734:     }\n735: }\n736: \n737: # Not published response\n738: {\n739:     \"status\": \"not_published\",\n740:     \"agent_name\": \"hello-agent\"\n741: }\n742: \n743: # Error response\n744: {\n745:     \"status\": \"error\",\n746:     \"error\": \"Docker is not available\"\n747: }\n748: ```\n749: \n750: ### Error Handling\n751: \n752: | Error | Source | CLI Output | Exit Code |\n753: |-------|--------|------------|-----------|\n754: | Metadata not found | `MetadataService.load_metadata` | `[red]Error fetching status: Metadata not found at {path}[/red]` | 1 |\n755: | Agent not published | `get_status` check | `[yellow]⚠ Agent has not been published[/yellow]` + guidance | 1 |\n756: | CR not found | `_get_cr_k8s_status` | `[red]Error fetching status: AgentRuntime 'xxx' not found...[/red]` | 1 |\n757: | K8s API error | `KubernetesProvider` | `[red]Error fetching status: {error}[/red]` | 1 |\n758: | Status error | CR/Deployment status | `[red]✗ Status error: {error}[/red]` | 1 |\n759: \n760: ## `DockerService` (`agentcube/services/docker_service.py`)\n761: \n762: ```python\n763: class DockerService:\n764:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n765:     def check_docker_available(self) -> bool: ...\n766:     def build_image(\n767:         self,\n768:         dockerfile_path: Path,\n769:         context_path: Path,\n770:         image_name: str,\n771:         tag: str = \"latest\",\n772:         build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n773:     ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n774:     def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n775:     def _get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n776:     def _format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str: ...\n777:     def push_image(\n778:         self,\n779:         image_name: str,\n780:         registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n781:         username: Optional[str] = None,\n782:         password: Optional[str] = None,\n783:     ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n784:     def _docker_login_sdk(self, registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str) -> None: ...\n785:     def _tag_image_sdk(self, source_image: str, target_image: str) -> None: ...\n786:     def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool: ...\n787: ```\n788: \n789: ## `MetadataService` (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n790: \n791: ```python\n792: class MetadataService:\n793:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n794:     def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n795:     def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n796:     def update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n797:     def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool: ...\n798:     def _validate_python_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n799:     def _validate_java_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n800: ```\n801: \n802: ## `KubernetesProvider` (`agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`)\n803: \n804: ```python\n805: class KubernetesProvider:\n806:     def __init__(\n807:         self,\n808:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n809:         verbose: bool = False,\n810:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n811:     ) -> None: ...\n812:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n813:     def deploy_agent(\n814:         self,\n815:         agent_name: str,\n816:         image_url: str,\n817:         port: int,\n818:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n819:         replicas: int = 1,\n820:         node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n821:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n822:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n823:     def _create_deployment(\n824:         self,\n825:         name: str,\n826:         image_url: str,\n827:         port: int,\n828:         entrypoint: Optional[str],\n829:         replicas: int,\n830:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n831:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n832:     def _create_service(self, name: str, port: int, node_port: Optional[int]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n833:     def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None: ...\n834:     def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n835:     def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n836:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str: ...\n837: ```\n838: \n839: ## `AgentCubeProvider` (`agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`)\n840: \n841: ```python\n842: class AgentCubeProvider:\n843:     def __init__(\n844:         self,\n845:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n846:         verbose: bool = False,\n847:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n848:     ) -> None: ...\n849:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n850:     def deploy_agent_runtime(\n851:         self,\n852:         agent_name: str,\n853:         image_url: str,\n854:         port: int,\n855:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n856:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n857:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n858:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n859:         readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n860:         readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n861:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n862:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str: ...\n863:     def get_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n864: ```\n865: \n866: CR API: `group=\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`, `version=\"v1alpha1\"`, `plural=\"agentruntimes\"`.\n867: \n868: ## `AgentMetadata` (Pydantic `BaseModel`)\n869: \n870: | Field | Type | Default | `Field(..., description=...)` |\n871: |-------|------|---------|--------------------------------|\n872: | `agent_name` | `str` | (required) | Unique name identifying the agent |\n873: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Human-readable summary |\n874: | `language` | `str` | `\"python\"` | Programming language used |\n875: | `entrypoint` | `str` | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n876